<!-- Backup Help --><div class="help-section"><nav class="help-breadcrumb"><a href="/help">Help</a> / <span>Backup & Restore</span></nav><h1><i class="fas fa-database"></i> Backup & Restore</h1><p class="help-intro">Protect your financial data.</p><div class="help-block"><h2>Why Backup?</h2><ul><li>Protect against data loss</li><li>Recover from accidental deletions</li><li>Required for audits and compliance</li><li>Peace of mind</li></ul></div><div class="help-block"><h2>Backup Types</h2><table class="help-table"><tr><td><strong>Manual Backup</strong></td><td>Click "Backup Now" anytime</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Automatic Backup</strong></td><td>Scheduled daily/weekly backups</td></tr></table></div><div class="help-block"><h2>Backup Settings</h2><ul><li><strong>Backup Directory</strong> - Where backups are stored</li><li><strong>Backup Schedule</strong> - Daily, weekly, monthly</li><li><strong>Backup Time</strong> - When automatic backups run</li><li><strong>Retention</strong> - How many backups to keep</li></ul></div><div class="help-block"><h2>Restore Process</h2><ol><li>Stop the application</li><li>Locate backup file (.db or .backup)</li><li>Replace current database with backup</li><li>Restart application</li></ol></div><div class="help-warning"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i><strong>Important:</strong> Store backups in multiple locations (local drive AND cloud storage).</div></div>
